<h2>
   Introduction to Trout Fishing Around Salem
</h2>
<p>
    Whether you're a seasoned fly fisher or just starting out, <strong>trout fishing near Salem, Oregon</strong> offers something for everyone. Nestled in the Willamette Valley, Salem is surrounded by rivers, creeks, and lakes teeming with trout. Anglers can target <strong>rainbow, cutthroat, brook, and even brown trout</strong> just minutes from downtown. The region’s well-managed stocking programs, scenic waters, and easy access make it a trout angler's dream.
</p>
<h2>
    Trout Species Found Near Salem, Oregon
</h2>
<p>
    Here are the most common trout species you’ll encounter:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rainbow Trout</strong>: The most widely stocked and caught species, available year-round.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Cutthroat Trout</strong>: Native to Oregon, found mostly in smaller streams and tributaries.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Brook Trout</strong>: High-elevation creeks and cold-water pockets.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Brown Trout</strong>: Less common but present in certain stretches of the North Santiam River.
    </li>
</ul>
