</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q3: Can I keep the trout I catch?</strong><br>
    If it’s a hatchery fish with a clipped fin and local regulations allow it, yes. Always check bag limits.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q4: What is the best time of year to fish for trout near Salem?</strong><br>
    Spring and fall are best, especially after stocking events.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q5: Are the rivers around Salem stocked with trout?</strong><br>
    Yes, especially the North Santiam and its tributaries.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Q6: Is trout fishing good for beginners?</strong><br>
    Absolutely! Stocked ponds and small lakes make learning easy and fun.
